<li><a href="2002#7january2002">7 January 2002</a></li>
</ul><h2 id="2december2002">Guide to Social Security Law Update 1476G # Date 2 December 2002</h2>
<p>All references to MAPA have been removed from the Guide as there are no current recipients and the last use of the payment was in mid 2001.</p>
<table summary="This table lists the pages changed for the 2 December 2002 release with details of the change"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Topic No</th>
<th scope="col">Topic Title</th>
<th scope="col">Details</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1.1.C.150</td>
<td>Chronic medical condition (CA)</td>
<td>Updated to ensure consistency with the revised Child Disability Assessment Determination.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.D.235</td>
<td>Domestic &amp; Family Violence (CrP)</td>
<td>Added definition of domestic and family violence.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.F.95</td>
<td>Fares Allowance</td>
<td>Changed number of return trips paid under FAA</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.H.72</td>
<td>Home invasion (CrP)</td>
<td>New definition.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.S.100</td>
<td>Severe disability (CA)</td>
<td>Updated to ensure consistency with the revised Child Disability Assessment Determination.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.2.1.10</td>
<td>New Start Allowance (NSA) - Description Parenting &amp; Employment Programs</td>
<td>Updated and clarified description of NSA.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.1.4.30</td>
<td>Payment after Release</td>
<td>Clarified processing of CrP for YA customers.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.1.70</td>
<td>Notification &amp; Recipient Obligations for NSA</td>
<td>Revised information on exemption from personal lodgement of statements.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.8.80</td>
<td>Work for the Dole</td>
<td>Revised whole topic.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.10.70</td>
<td>YA Study Load - Full-time Tertiary Students</td>
<td>Clarified full-time study where there is a HECS anomaly.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.3.4.20</td>
<td>Austudy &amp; Full-time Tertiary Students Youth &amp; Students</td>
<td>Clarified full-time study where there is a HECS anomaly.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.3.4.60</td>
<td>Assessing Tertiary Study Load for Austudy</td>
<td>Clarified full-time study where there is a HECS anomaly.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.4.2.50</td>
<td>Continuation, Variation or Termination of WP</td>
<td>Amended example under payment of WP to partners of DVA disability pensioners.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.5.1.180</td>
<td>Participation Support - Participation Interview Types</td>
<td>Clarified cases where attendance is optional rather than compulsory.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.1.100</td>
<td>Continuation, Variation or Termination of DSP</td>
<td>Clarified that payment of DSP must be suspended or cancelled if the customer is in custody pending trial or in gaol or psychiatric confinement.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.5.10</td>
<td>Qualification for SA</td>
<td>Included information about customers on graduated return to work.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.5.50</td>
<td>Payability of SA - Payments from Employer</td>
<td>Included information about customers on graduated return to work.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.5.110</td>
<td>Continuation, Variation or Termination of SA</td>
<td>Included information about customers on graduated return to work.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.8.25</td>
<td>CDAT Steps 2-4 - Developmentally-linked Functional Domains</td>
<td>Updated to ensure consistency with the revised Child Disability Assessment Determination.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.4.30</td>
<td>Qualification for CrP - Extreme Circumstances (other)</td>
<td>Added examples of home invasions and abusive neighbours.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.4.50</td>
<td>Payability of CrP - Extreme Circumstances (domestic &amp; family violence)</td>
<td>Amended domestic and family violence examples.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.4.60</td>
<td>Payability of CrP - Extreme circumstances (other)</td>
<td>Added example of home invasion.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.8.3.50</td>
<td>Assessing Tertiary Study Load for PES</td>
<td>Clarified full-time study load.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.2.9.30</td>
<td>Family Actual Means Test - Amounts not included in Family Actual Means Test</td>
<td>Corrected example under Dependent Children Income.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.2.9.50</td>
<td>Current Family Actual Means Test - Current Family Actual Means Test Assessment</td>
<td>Updated year references in examples.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.2.31</td>
<td>Other Income Exempt from Assessment - Specifically Approved</td>
<td>Added to lump sums exempted under section 8(11).</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.6.30</td>
<td>Restitution Payments Germany &amp; Austria</td>
<td>Added information on pensions payable from employment in s Ghetto (ZRGB).</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.9.3.10</td>
<td>Income Assessment of Assets-test Exempt Income Streams</td>
<td>Clarified relevant number of life expectancy income streams.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.12.4.20</td>
<td>Excluded Assets of Controlled Private Trusts &amp; Controlled Private Companies</td>
<td>Clarified excluded assets of controlled private trusts and controlled private companies.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.12.5.30</td>
<td>Apportioning a Liability of a Controlled Private Company or Controlled Private Trust</td>
<td>Clarified apportioning a loan or encumbrance.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.12.7.30</td>
<td>Transfers of the Capital of a Private Trust or Private Company</td>
<td>Updated policy, changing 'distribution' to 'transfer'.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.12.7.50</td>
<td>Distributions of the Income of a Private Trust or Private Company to a Non-attributable Stakeholder</td>
<td>Clarified distributions paid to non-attributable stakeholders on or after 1 July 2000.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.13.1.30</td>
<td>Effect of Compensation on Compensation Affected Payments</td>
<td>Added that some additional payments are also compensation affected payments.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.13.2.50</td>
<td>Aggregation of Multiple Lump Sums</td>
<td>Clarified aggregation of mixtures of settlement types.</td>
</tr><tr><td>5.2.6.30</td>
<td>RAA - May 1984 to Present Date</td>
<td>Added rates for circumstances where the partner is illness separated, in respite care or in gaol.</td>
</tr><tr><td>6.7.2.30</td>
<td>Debt Recovery by Deductions</td>
<td>Clarified debt recovery by deductions following legal advice.</td>
</tr><tr><td>6.7.2.40</td>
<td>Debt Recovery by Legal Proceedings</td>
<td>Clarified debt recovery by deductions following legal advice.</td>
</tr><tr><td>6.7.2.50</td>
<td>Debt Recovery by Garnishee Notice</td>
<td>Clarified debt recovery by deductions following legal advice.</td>
</tr><tr><td>6.7.3.80</td>
<td>Waiver of Debt on the Basis of Notional Entitlement</td>
<td>Clarified debt recovery by deductions following legal advice.</td>
</tr><tr><td>10.3</td>
<td>Agreement with the United Kingdom</td>
<td>New chapter.</td>
</tr></tbody></table><h2 id="4november2002">Guide to Social Security Law Update 1475G # Date 4 November 2002</h2>
<p>All references to MAPA have been removed from the Guide as there are no current recipients and the last use of the payment was in mid 2001.</p>
<table summary="This table lists the pages changed for the 4 November 2002 release with details of the change"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Topic No</th>
<th scope="col">Topic Title</th>
<th scope="col">Details</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1.1.A.290</td>
<td>Asset</td>
<td>Clarified details of gifts above $10,000 included as financial investments.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.D.80</td>
<td>Dependent child (YA)</td>
<td>Amended the definition of dependent child (YA).</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.D.90</td>
<td>Dependent child (for YA independence purposes only)</td>
<td>Amended the definition of dependent child (for YA independence purposes only).</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.2.2.20</td>
<td>Mature Age Allowance (MAA) &amp; Mature Age Partner Allowance (MAPA) - Former Payment - Description</td>
<td>Amended to reflect that MAPA is not a current payment.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.1.5.50</td>
<td>Bereavement Payments for Couples where One Member is a DVA Customer</td>
<td>Amended to enable payment of bereavement payments for partners of war widow(er) (DVA) pensioners.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.9.10</td>
<td>Temporary Incapacity Activity Test Exemption</td>
<td>Added extra information on the Personal Adviser's role with customers seeking a temporary incapacity activity test exemption.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.10.60</td>
<td>YA Study Load - Full-time Secondary Students</td>
<td>Corrected policy in regard to 5 day absences.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.7.160</td>
<td>Backdating Commencement Day for CA</td>
<td>Corrected information about CA (child) HCC only and backdating.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.2.70</td>
<td>SpB for Customers Under 18 Years of Age</td>
<td>Updated homeless requirement for Australian citizen children.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.2.80</td>
<td>SpB for Australian Citizen Children in the Custody of a Non-permanent Resident</td>
<td>Updated homeless requirement for Australian citizen children.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.9.1.80</td>
<td>Start Day for HCC - Claim Required</td>
<td>Corrected legislative reference.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.2.9.30</td>
<td>Family Actual Means Test - Amounts not included in Family Actual Means Test</td>
<td>Amended policy for amounts not included for isolated or secondary boarders.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.6.6.10</td>
<td>General Provisions for Valuation of Assets</td>
<td>Clarified general provisions for valuation of assets.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.7.2.20</td>
<td>Assessable Assets from Private Companies &amp; Unlisted Public Companies</td>
<td>Clarified details of the net asset backing method of valuing shares from private and unlisted public companies.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.9.1.25</td>
<td>Joint Income Streams</td>
<td>Added new topic.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.13.1.10</td>
<td>What is Compensation</td>
<td>Clarified treatment of overseas compensation.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.13.1.50</td>
<td>Exemptions from the Compensation Provisions</td>
<td>Amended to refelect legal opinion that ther are no saved provisions for transfers from SCAP's to CAP's.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.13.2.50</td>
<td>Aggregation of Multiple Lump-Sums</td>
<td>Added details regarding commencement dates for aggregation provisions.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.13.3.30</td>
<td>Effect of Periodic Compensation on the Partner of a Compensation Recipient</td>
<td>Clarified effect of income on the calculation of the excess compensation for the partner.</td>
</tr><tr><td>6.2.1.10</td>
<td>Types of NSA &amp; Unemployed YA Reviews</td>
<td>Updated for changes to the review regime for temporary incapacity exemption reviews.</td>
</tr><tr><td>6.4.7</td>
<td>Recovery Rules Specific to Lump-Sums</td>
